# React Rules

## Components

- Use functional components only.
- Keep components focused on a single responsibility.
- Prefer composition over prop drilling.
- Extract reusable UI immediately when repeated more than once.
- Avoid components larger than ~200 lines.
- Keep JSX clean and readable.

---

## File Structure

- One component per file.
- Group related files together.
- Keep assets, hooks, constants and utilities separate.
- Avoid dumping everything into one folder.

---

## State

- Keep state as local as possible.
- Do not lift state unless multiple components truly need it.
- Avoid unnecessary useState.
- Derive values instead of storing derived state.
- Prefer useMemo/useCallback only when they provide measurable benefit.

---

## Props

- Keep props minimal.
- Avoid passing unused props.
- Use descriptive prop names.
- Avoid deeply nested props.

---

## Rendering

- Avoid unnecessary re-renders.
- Never create components inside another component unless required.
- Move repeated JSX into reusable components.

---

## JSX

- Keep JSX declarative.
- Avoid deeply nested ternaries.
- Prefer early returns.
- Break large JSX into smaller components.

---

## Imports

- Remove unused imports.
- Group imports consistently.
- Prefer absolute imports if configured.

---

## Styling

- Do not use inline styles unless dynamic.
- Keep styling consistent across components.
- Reuse utility classes instead of repeating long class lists.

---

## Performance

- Lazy load large sections when appropriate.
- Optimize images.
- Prefer SVG icons.
- Avoid unnecessary dependencies.

---

## Code Quality

- Use meaningful variable names.
- Use descriptive component names.
- Avoid magic numbers.
- Extract repeated constants.
- Remove dead code.
- Remove console.log before completion.

---

## Accessibility

- Use semantic HTML.
- Add aria-labels where required.
- Always include alt text.
- Ensure keyboard accessibility.
- Maintain proper heading hierarchy.

---

## Animations

- Keep animations subtle.
- Animate only meaningful interactions.
- Avoid animation-heavy interfaces.
- Respect prefers-reduced-motion when possible.

---

## Forms

- Use controlled components.
- Validate inputs cleanly.
- Keep form state organized.

---

## Hooks

- Follow Rules of Hooks.
- Keep custom hooks reusable.
- Extract complex logic into hooks.

---

## Project Standards

- Prefer reusable components over duplicated JSX.
- Keep files small.
- Keep logic separate from presentation when complexity grows.
- Write production-ready code only.

---

## Before Finishing

Verify:

□ No unused code

□ No console logs

□ No duplicate JSX

□ Clean component structure

□ Responsive layout

□ Accessible markup

□ Readable code

□ Reusable components

□ Consistent naming

□ Production-ready implementation